# Laravel Passport

## When to use

- Implementing a full OAuth2 server in Laravel
- Authorization code, PKCE, device flow, client credentials, or personal access tokens
- Third-party app authentication with scopes
- Choosing between Passport (OAuth2) and Sanctum (simple tokens)

## Keywords

`passport`, `oauth2`, `authorization code`, `PKCE`, `client credentials`, `personal access token`, `scopes`, `HasApiTokens`, `laravel/passport`, `install:api --passport`
